OL,6,FThere is no specific law to ban where
OL,7,Fthey can be used, and the Department
OL,8,Ffor Health and Social Care says it
OL,9,Fcurrently has no plans to introduce
OL,10,Frestrictions as "there is no evidence
OL,11,Fto suggest second-hand vapour causes
OL,12,Fwider health harms in the way tobacco
OL,13,Fsmoke does."
OL,15,FAlthough the government does add
OL,16,Femployers or operators of indoor
OL,17,Fspaces are within their rights to
OL,18,Fimplement policies banning the use of
OL,19,Fvapes in their premises.
